cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image-based material capture using deep learning techniques. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with capturing the appearance of real-world materials, which is relevant to computer graphics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses deep learning techniques to estimate material appearance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with intelligent systems that can estimate material appearance from a variable number of uncalibrated and unordered pictures. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with capturing material appearance from multiple images, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
